  , issueCommentBody =
      "About the first error message, this is related to https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/2463\r\n\r\nSince 1.13 (and especially the introduction of `r.args`), the JavaScript drivers lets the server handle arity errors, and they currently works for methods that would behave like `r.getAll(r.table(\"comments\"), key1, key2)`.\r\n\r\n\r\nOne way to avoid your error is to do something like\r\n\r\n````\r\nr.table('comments').filter(...)('user').distinct().do(function(users) {\r\n    return r.branch(\r\n        users.count().eq(0),\r\n        [], // users is an empty. array, so we just return an empty array\r\n        r.table('users').getAll(users)\r\n     )\r\n})\r\n```"
  , issueCommentId = 46806390
